Package berlin.hu.cep.connector

Class ConnectorConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • berlin.hu.cep.connector.ConnectorConfig
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MongoDBConnectConfig, ZeebeConfig
    public abstract class ConnectorConfig
extends Object
    An abstract class for Kafka Connect configurations.

    As an attribute of a @ConnectorPostObject it can be send to a Kafka Connectinstance via a POST-methode of the Kafka Connect-REST-API.

    Author:
    Lukas Gehring, Leon Haussknecht, Maurice Lindner, Jost Hermann Triller, Stefan Zabka
    See Also:
    Kafka Connect Dokumentation

      • getTasks_max

        public int getTasks_max()
        Returns tasks.max (the maximum number of tasks that should be created for this connector. The connector may create fewer tasks if it cannot achieve this level of parallelism) (https://docs.confluent.io/current/connect/managing/configuring.html)
        Returns:
        the tasks_max

      • getKey_converter

        public String getKey_converter()
        Returns key.converter (Converter class for key Connect data. This controls the format of the data that will be written to Kafka for source connectors or read from Kafka for sink connectors. Popular formats include Avro and JSON.) (https://docs.confluent.io/current/connect/references/allconfigs.html#connect-allconfigs)
        Returns:
        the key_converter
